g.aria-label: This PCB (â€œBEEF BRIDGE V1.0) was designed by me, Jaro Habiger during my Covid Quarantine in July 2022. It is an IGBT Half bridge that can handle High Voltages (450V) and high current (15A Hot, 30A Cold). The board also features an LC-lowpass-filter, that has a cutoff frequency of about 20khz. The purpose of this board is to serve as the Power-Stage of a beefy class-d audio amplifier. The design is open hardware and licensed under CERN-OHL-S and the design files can be accessed under https://github.com/anuejn/beef_bridge
